--> Jenkins is the open source Continuous Integration (CI) server
--> Server is http://localhost:8080 or http://localhost:9090
--> Download Generic Java Package (.war) file and install using command 'java -jar jenkins.war'
--> Once Jenkins is running, you can access it local host

*** Integration with Selenium FW ***
--> Create a new project folder for selenium FW, in that folder give our local path of selenium directory
--> Give command to run the testt by going in required folders, here you can use environment variables to shorten our commands
--> In commands, you can also give command for generating html report with folder path
--> Save the project
--> Go to that project folder, click 'Build Now' it will start execution
--> We can configure Jenkins with choice parameterized while running for eg. In which browser test should be run

--> To create xml report of test results, how many test passed or failed
    --> So first need to export all the test results as XML file, run with command '-v --junitxml=result.xml'
    --> In Configuration --> Add Post Build Option --> Publish JUnit test result report --> Give the path of exported result.xml file --> Save the project
    --> Now start the build --> When build is completed a 'latest Test Result' report will be created there --> Open and see how many test cases were failed or passed or skip